column1: Who will win the 2020 Michigan Democratic primary?
column5: ['Joe Biden', 'Michael Bloomberg', 'Pete Buttigieg', 'Amy Klobuchar', 'Bernie Sanders', 'Elizabeth Warren', 'Someone else']
column6: ['Elections and Referenda']
Blowout. Game over. https://www.realclearpolitics.com/epolls/2020/president/mi/michigan_democratic_presidential_primary-6835.htmlYou

Biden has the backing of Union bosses and most black people, while Sander's has the backing of SOME regular union members and younger black voters. Sanders is a making a LARGE push into MI and ignoring MO. It will boil down to who can make the bigger turn-out play, but the numbers HIGHLY favor Biden.
Biden has consolidated his ownership of the Democratic establishment

https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2020-primary-forecast/michigan/

In my previous forecast, I stated that Bernie Sanders would win the 2020 Michigan Democratic primary. I made that forecast when Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar and Michael Bloomberg were still in the race. Since then, much has change. It seems that the momentum is in Joe Biden's favor. Even though Bernie Sanders won the Michigan Democratic primary in 2016, this time looks different given the recent events.

Adjusting upward from my previous forecast of 75%. Endorsements from Gov. Whitmer and Lt. Gov. Gilchrist. https://www.woodtv.com/news/elections/why-whitmer-gilchrist-endorsed-biden/ FiveThirtyEight now has the former VP as a 77% favorite to win. https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2020-primary-forecast/michigan/
Using 438 as baseline: https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2020-primary-forecast/michigan/
https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2020-primary-forecast/michigan/

In spite of Sen. Sanders’ victory here four years ago, Vice President Biden has an advantage in the polls and he and his former opponents who’ve since endorsed him combine for 49%. https://www.realclearpolitics.com/epolls/2020/president/mi/michigan_democratic_presidential_primary-6835.html
Updating based on Biden surge on Super Tuesday.
https://www.clickondetroit.com/decision-2020/2020/03/04/poll-where-michigan-voters-stand-ahead-of-the-2020-democratic-primary-election/
Using Prediction Market [https://www.predictit.org/markets/detail/6038].
Flipping the odds after Biden's turnaround.

Like many of the other states we are waiting for more polls to re-calibrate our predictions. We do have one recent poll from Michigan though which gives Biden a 7% lead. I suspect this is fairly accurate as this is the kind of lead Biden had before Sanders had his bounce after Iowa.

If Biden can win Minnesota I expect he can win Michigan, and if you look at the polling numbers the moderates definitely seem to have the numbers if they can focus on 1 candidate (which will now be Biden, as a result of super Tuesday).
Will adjust forecast again after Super Tuesday and also watch for new Michigan polling.
https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2020-primary-forecast/michigan/
Adjusting in light of Buttigieg dropping out.
Updating due to Buttigieg Dropping

This will be a tight contest between traditional Democratic voters who will lean towards Biden, and disaffected voters who went for Trump last time and will see Sanders as the alternative to the traditional politicians.

For this forecast, I used the crowd forecast, the prediction market [1] and the latest state poll (if available) reported in RealClear Politics [2]. I scaled the forecast to the top 3 candidates only. [1] https://www.predictit.org/markets/detail/6038 [2] https://www.realclearpolitics.com/

Bernie Sanders won the Michigan primary in 2016. He won most of the lower income counties in Michigan. I can only assume that he would win the 2020 primary based on the momentum he got since he won the Nevada primary.

Sanders will repeat 2016 in Michigan. His backers may not be the majority of the party but they will get out and vote and they will be a large enough plurality to win the contest.
